{"article_id":"jrdWfdLVgkb62EIM","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Senate gave sweeping bipartisan approval Thursday to a proposal by Orrin Hatch , R-Utah , and Amy Klobuchar , D-Minn. ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"to put senators on record in favor","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"of repealing a tax on medical devices","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"- a key part of President Obama ' s controversial health care law .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"The Hatch-Klobuchar amendment to the GOP budget plan is the latest effort","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"to roll back the tax","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"that applies to a range of medical products , from surgical tools to heart devices .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"It ' s among several taxes in Obama ' s 2010 health care overhaul .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"The amendment passed the Senate by a vote of 79 to 20 .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"The bill","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that it was attached to","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"did not pass ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"but the sponsors used it as an opportunity","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"to rally support","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"for repealing the tax","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"-- as well as a separate bill","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"they 've introduced","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"to achieve that .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"\" Today , bipartisan members of the Senate spoke loudly and clearly","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"that this tax on medical devices simply must go .","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"It is a drain on innovation , on job creation and on our ability","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"to provide ground breaking medical technologies to patients , \"","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"Hatch said in a statement .","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"The Affordable Care Act levies a 2.3 percent tax on medical devices with the goal","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"of raising nearly $ 30 billion over the next decade .","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"Manufacturers say","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"the impact of the tax is far greater","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"than meets the eye","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"-- the 2.3 percent tax is on gross sales ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"meaning it 's a much greater percentage of net income .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"The Obama administration has defended the medical device tax ,","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"companies actually stand to benefit from the law .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Though the 2.3 percent tax hits the industry ,","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"the department argues","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"that the millions of new health care customers","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"insured","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"as a result of the law","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"will increase the demand in hospitals","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"to order more equipment","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"-- in turn boosting medical device companies ' profits .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Last year the White House threatened to veto a House bill","depth":3},{"id":42,"text":"that would have repealed the tax ,","depth":3},{"id":43,"text":"citing concerns","depth":4},{"id":44,"text":"that the House proposal would offset the lost revenue from the tax","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"by cutting down on subsidies for some families .","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"This ,","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"they said ,","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"would effectively `` raise taxes on middle-class and low-income families . ''","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":97,"left":89,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":71,"right":88,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":71,"left":66,"right":70,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":66,"left":57,"right":65,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":57,"left":56,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":56,"left":52,"right":55,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{